title: Totally Full Frontal
overview: Totally Full Frontal was a spinoff of the 1993 popular comedy sketch show Full Frontal. The show was only created when Full Frontal ended the year before as an attempt to keep Australian sketch comedy alive. The show introduced new actors including Vic Plume, Julia Zemiro and Paul McCarthy. The show also stared two actors from Full Frontal who were Ross Williams and Paul Walker.
